citations:
    citation-agot-arya-iv:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Arya IV"
            text_from_source: "Syrio Forel stepped between them, tapping his wooden sword lightly against his boot. 'You will be stopping there. Are you men or dogs that you would threaten a child?' … 'The first sword of Braavos does not run,' he sang as Ser Meryn slashed at him."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Ser Meryn Trant arrives with five Lannister guardsmen to seize Arya during her final lesson with Syrio Forel. Syrio fights them all with a wooden practice sword, killing or disabling five guardsmen, allowing Arya to escape. Syrio faces Ser Meryn alone with a broken stick — his fate is left ambiguous. Arya escapes through the Red Keep, finds Hullen (Winterfell master of horse) dying in the stable, kills a stableboy who tries to stop her, and escapes through the underground dragon skull passage. Hullen, Desmond, and other Stark guards are found dead."
